Get into 4 Groups...

MyFoodBag is good. But can we do a broader cart ? A biiger cart like amazon.
Can you get a more generic name ?
Food can be one of the categories. 

Pink Nav Bar, And Beige Body Color is perfect.

TASK 1:
Install bootstrap and angular-bootstrap

> npm install bootstrap ngx-bootstrap --save

TASK 1a:

Update ypur app.module by including the following new bootstrap modules at the appropriate place.

...
import { BsDropdownModule } from 'ngx-bootstrap/dropdown';
import { TooltipModule } from 'ngx-bootstrap/tooltip';
import { ModalModule } from 'ngx-bootstrap/modal';
...
...

@NgModule({
  imports: [
    BrowserModule,
    BsDropdownModule.forRoot(),
    TooltipModule.forRoot(),
    ModalModule.forRoot()
  ],
  // ...
})
export class AppModule {}

...

Task 2:

We need to create 18-24 Product Items.
Divide yourselves into 4 groups. 

Each group should do 6 products. One from each of the below. 
Gather the images too for the same. 
Save your images in your assets folder. 

The categories are fixed.

Clothing - 1
Books - 2
Jewelry - 3
Stationary - 4
Furniture - 5
Food & Grocery - 6

The food and grocery does not exist. Create it. 

